The nursery school is also part of the offices including the architects.
The Avriopoint administrative building of Brno is the new headquarters of the company Arch. Design.
No one could have expected it to also house a mini nursery school with everything - color walls, imaginative furniture, toys and finally a miniature playground on the terrace.
Since October last year, the children of Arch. design employees can go there.
The architectural project company Arch. Design. whose workshops produced a large number of constructions in Brno, has imagined its mini nursery business school since the first drafts of the Avriopoint building.
It employed about 90 people, especially the age of children, and it was important that women architects and project managers should be able to return to work quickly.
Along with reduced-time employment contracts, the nursery school is a bonus offered to its employees by the company Arch. Design. as part of its social program.
Manufacturers and architects thus have the opportunity to combine work that takes care of children.
It was the employees of Arch.Design.themselves who conceived this nursery school and with the support of the management they were able to obtain an endowment from the European Union and the Ministry of Labour and Social Affairs.
The mini nursery school is financed by the European Social Fund through the operational human resources programme and the State Budget of the Czech Republic.
Thanks to the funding (up to 2.8 million Czech kroons), they were able to buy equipment and equipment and after two years provide qualified staff and start up.
After the use of the funding endowment (two years) the company Arch. Design. has an obligation after 3 years to operate the mini nursery school from its own funds.
The preparation of the project lasted one year and it was Economy rating that helped to apply for the staffing.
Child care is provided by qualified staff, a nurse and a kindergarten teacher take care of children all day long. Children can go to nursery school without age limitation, but they are over three years old for the most part.
As it is a "mini nursery school" there can only be 5 children present at the same time, but during the day there are more who are replacing each other.
The operation of the school is flexible according to the needs of the parents and the children of all employees have the same right to use the school without regard to the hierarchical position.
Although individual care and education are provided, the curriculum of the mini-nursery school is comparable to that for pre-school education.
Children are not only playing but also providing quality teaching - from the beginning to preparation for school schools, English is taught.
The class is equipped not only with imaginative toys and games, but also with a computer that children can use.
The presence of small children in society creates a friendly and positive environment.
Parents may at any time control their child and do not have the stress of being delayed to pick up the children in a school away from the parents' place of work.
Parents therefore use their working time in the most productive way.
It is not surprising that there is a natural relationship of loyalty between the employee and the employer.
Arch.Design.has thus registered among the companies that offer a bonus of choice for the recruitment of new employees and who are friendly to the family and through this program strengthens the marketing of HR.
The bone house still fascinates after 100 years. Take a look in Gaudi's interiors.
The roof resembles the back of a prehistoric saurian, the staircase with a dinosaur spine and the balconies with open fish gules.
This is the Casa Battlo house in Barcelona by architect Antoni Gaudi.
Due to its organic forms, the house was given the nickname "Bone House" from the premises.
Organic shapes, wild colours, unusual use of stones, fragments of tiles and mosaics, facade reminiscent of scales and everywhere present of curves, this is all that is ypic for Antoni Gaudi's Art Nouveau.
The front façade of the house unfolds its dream lines, pleasant colours and textures that remind nature and animals.
During a more detailed observation we see the geometry, the rhythm and the order thought with precision.
In the night the facade of the house becomes even more dramatic and is lit in such a way that the impression of brightness of the colors is strengthened.
The winding and twisting of the shapes also appears in the interiors with the same measure.
Wood is a wave copy of window frames, balustrades, door decorative elements, eyelet and slats.
The Battlo house, which stands in the Eixample district on Passeig de Gracia street at the number 43, was the result of the construction of an 1877 house by the architect Emilio Sala Cortes.
The reconstruction took place for two years and the house was completed in 1906.
The investor, Joseph Battlo, a wealthy entrepreneur, first insisted on the demolition of the old construction and the construction of another brand new one but quickly accepted Gaudi's idea of an unusual reconstruction and cheaper.
But the idea of Casa Battlo as a multi-dwelling house was not thought by Gaudi alone.
Architect Josep Maria Jujol worked with him.
It was precisely on his project that the decorations for an apartment representing the owner of the building and the use of mosaics for the façade were born.
For the façade also worked other artists and creators.
The joint work for the plans of Casa Battlo started with a successful cooperation between Jujol and Gaudi.
Jujol participated in the construction of the house of Gaudi Casa Mila and Guell Park in which there are other works of Gaudi.
The locals nicknamed the house hot just after its finish because of its organic forms "the Bone House."
Others, considering the specific mechanism of opening windows, called it "the house that bails."
It is said that at the top of the construction there is a sword similar to that of Saint George the patron of Catalonia.
Other building sculpture elements contain hidden religious motifs.
Gaudi thought for the house a system unique in its central heating time, with ventilation vents and typical chimneys.
Their 45-degree inclination seems odd.
During the creation Gaudi absolutely did not comply with the then construction directives and did not let themselves be obstructed by them.
At the beginning of the construction he obtained from the city the building permit, knowing, of course, that the data put on the reconstruction plans were so vague that two years later during the finish the city council was horrified and asked for modifications.
For example, the members of the municipal council were not pleased that the building pillars were encroaching on the public sidewalk.
There was never any change, but, on the contrary, only 15 days after the call of the city Josep Battlo asked (and obtained satisfaction) for permission to rent the two highest floors.
The owner moved to the lower floors.
In the gallery on the second floor there was a common living room and on the third there was a bedroom and a private part of the apartment.
The ground floor was rented to a jewellery store.
The entire six-storey house is shared by a staircase through which you can access to an independent roof terrace.
All right angles and straight lines were cancelled by the basic elements of the reconstruction and their replacement by curved walls.
Gaudi also worked on the modern concept of linking spaces.
The common part can be completely connected by opening the doors of the salons and the high society can communicate comfortably or confine itself to private space for more intimate interviews.
The house with the reconstruction of Gaudi received besides new facades a non-traditional roof and two more floors.
Gaudi's play with light is also impressive, blue and white glazed tiles with which is decorated the inner courtyard and with the light wells.
The two-color game gives a maximum of light in all floors of the house.
It was enough simply to bet on the principle that white reflects more than dark which, on the contrary, absorbs the rays of the sun.
Casa Battlo House which was registered in 2005 in the UNESCO World Heritage Fund can be visited by everyone.
On the first floor of the house is the most spacious and splendid apartment accessible to the public.
The owners decided to take this step in 2002 on the occasion of the 150th anniversary of the birth of the famous creator.
They continued the visits because they found it to be a lucrative undertaking and extended the scope of the visits to common spaces and attic including roof terraces.
The entrance ticket to the monument is really cheap and costs 16.50 euros; students, pensioners, groups and holders of tourist cards have 20 percent discount.
The sum is still above the entry price in the other buildings of Gaudi in the city.
If you want to feel the real atmosphere of the house with its fantastic turrets, you must quickly find a comrade among the residents of the building and visit the house completely.
How to choose a mattress and a spring: women have other criteria than men.
No ostentatious frame, but rather the quality of the bed area, so the mattress and the bed rest give a real basis for a good bed.
They must of course complement each other harmoniously to please a concrete user.
During the choice several things are decisive: weight, height, age, health status as well as the sex of the owner.
The type of interior in which the mattress and spring are to be placed is also important.
A typical example?
For example, in the country house where latex mattresses are not sleeping continuously, they are not suitable because they are slowly "warming up."
They also have a weight higher than standard polyurethane mattresses.
It is necessary to return them frequently.
If they also do not have enough ventilation channels in the heart and if they remain on a solid board, they retain moisture. Mold can also form there.
The habit is also decisive in the choice.
Those who spend the light of time abroad where very thick mattresses are frequently used with a softening layer, will hardly feel well on a low and hard surface.
"That's how all the hokeyists coming back from NHL complain that they can't sleep there."
"For their tired shoulders, feet and ribs, they needed mattresses with a swollen layer of lazy foam."
"Such mattresses are also recommended for people suffering from diabetes who have a nervous system disorder which therefore ill assume" information "of the joints and skin," explains Sylva Adamczikova who specializes in upholstered furniture.
That's why a few years ago the mattress with lazy foam conquered the hokeyists as well as other customers.
"Today everything works well, Tempur, the Italian Magnifex but also the Czech Tropico, for example, have suitable mattresses.
You don't need to be an NHL guy to enjoy a lazy foam.
This "miracle" simply works.
It optimizes its rigidity and shape according to the heat absorbed or adapts to the heat of your body.
Nothing puts pressure on you and you won't turn around in the night like after a tough game.
You're just sleeping better.
The lazy foam also works as a protection against squirrels.
To choose the mattress according to your size, add the length of the feet, about 21 / 34 cm.
A man and a woman of a size of 180cm therefore need a bed of 210 / 220 cm.
The minimum width for each one for a double bed should be 90 cm or 180 cm in total.
For single beds, for example singles, it is recommended to take at least 120 / 140 cm.
It's convenient in case of a visit.
'However it is a simple rule for the width of the bed: when you are lying on your back you should pose your hands comfortably with the slightly folded elbows. Helena Prokopova, President of the Association of Pailors and Decorators who has been dedicated for several years to the problem of a healthy sleep and the ergonomics of furniture and teaches it in specialized schools.
For a double bed each needs its own bed bed and mattress, so be careful during the purchase to choose the height of the mattress.
Otherwise you will only have to climb the spring at different heights and this is not feasible on all the bed frames.
Foam mattresses should have a minimum height of 14 cm, spring mattresses at least 15 cm, so count for the shape and aeration layer at least three cm.
"With touch or sitting on the mattress you should not feel the springs," warns Helena Prokopova.
Each mattress requires a specific type of spring.
The bed-bed, when the mattress and the bed-bed are united as Siamese sisters, has nothing to do in the bedrooms.
The mattresses were very badly ventilated; it should not be washed, which is common today.
And since during the night it is normally sweaty from 0.2 to 0.75 l of sweat it is clear that after 5 / 7 years, the mattress begins to remind a large (and clogged) sieve.
For this purpose specialists refuse to make a claim over a life of 25 years for a mattress or a lifetime warranty.
But everything to her but.
And for this, an expert advice from the vendors: for a 120 / 140cm mattress, give up hygiene or washing for the mattress coating, but instead add a protective mattress that you can easily remove and wash.
And even if nowadays it is common to make coatings with zipper for the whole set, that is, after opening one has two parts (for washing and the size of the washing machine it is very important!) otherwise the handling for large models (and for one person only) becomes when they are removed a fight between a light weight and a heavy weight on a ring.
Do you have a stiff board in your bed instead of a spring?
Never!
Maximum for a bed intended for visitors for one night only.
However, equip the board (if there are none) with ventilation holes and use the spring mattress with a minimum height of 15cm with bag springs (from Germany Taschenfederken) and a ventilation layer.
A polyurethane mattress must not be part of such a bed.
For single-position slats with 14 / 18 slats, latex mattresses or so-called sandwiches (perhaps the combination of latex and coconut) are ideal but it will always be better for you to have a mattress with more slats, 28 and above, where the slats are doubled in the lower part of the kidneys and it is thus possible to regulate their rigidity.
For multi-position mattresses it is not necessary to take a spring mattress because it does not respond to the changes in position.
Alongside the adjustment of the stiffness of the slats it is also possible to install what is called a shoulder cradle.
This is a special connection of the slats that allows to pressure or even tilt the slats so that the shoulder of the sleeper "fits well."
For men who have "shoulders as wide as the back," this is really an important thing.
This thing is already envisaged by the mattress manufacturers who for "males" have started to use a softening area at the shoulders.
But they also think of women - they again offer them a softer surface at the hip level.
For the most difficult customer there are wing or platelet springs with what is called a multiforce suspension.
Pressure spreads into more points and spreads the tension.
But of course, be careful, as soon as you use a bad pillow (large and air-swollen) on good mattresses and spring, the "plus" disappear.
The basic rule is a simple pillow: the pillow must support the head and its tips must reach only the shoulders, so that the muscles of the shoulders can rest.
The recommended size is 50X60 cm that Scandinavians prefer by exmple.
When lying on the side, the pillow must level (with the shoulder cradle of the spring or the area softened in the mattress) the height of the shoulders.
Modern mattresses still have something in common with the first ones made from straw and herbs.
Manufacturers still use natural materials or mixtures.
The trend is also with organic mattresses.
Petrol-based raw materials, from which polyurethane is produced, are replaced by natural oils, such as soya oil.
Almost all known manufacturers use soybeans.
"The Bio qualifier for mattresses means that the heart is made from natural products," explains Petr vasicek of Tropico Plus.
Natural materials are also used for mattress coatings; one of the first was aloe vera.
But you can add micro-capsules that develop forest or lavender fragrances.
There are differences between men and women.
While the birch plant extract so that the mattress coating absorbs heat and cools the body, "cools" man, the coatings "heats" women.
Red pepper extract accelerates blood circulation and is therefore warmer for the weaker sex.
The current favorites?
Mattresses made from cold foam (it has more pores with a disturbed cell structure so more breathable than the standard polyurethane and has more elasticity.
The combination of different rigidities of cold foams gives polyzone mattresses that know precisely where the head, lower back and feet are.
You will pay a quality mattress from 7000 crowns and over.
Those that are characterised by their health parameters have less VAT and are taken as instruments for health.
In the Czech Republic, Gumotex reached first place.
It is not easy to save for the mattress and the spring.
It is possible from time to time to have two mattresses in special actions by manufacturers or producers for the price of one.
Like for example Magniflex, which offers Duofreeze mattresses with memory foam sewn to the coating for 11990 crowns.
We can obviously take the second one for free.
The era of lazy or viscoelastic foams with an open cell structure and a great thickness was started with Tempur material at a "cosmic" rate.
This began as a matter for NASA because astronauts were experiencing enormous load factors at startup.
Tempur grows warm and hardens in the cold.
It therefore adapts perfectly to the warm human body and distributes an optimal pressure to it.
For this it is ideal against sleeping ill and for an increase of comfort during sleep.
Viscoelastic foams are used not only for mattresses but also for health products, such as special foot cushions that relieve the legs and venous system.
For example, Czech manufacturers use EucathermC or Twinsaver foam or similar foam.
The devices to track people are increasingly being requested by parents who want to monitor their children.
Fear for their child is leading more and more people to think about watching them through a GPS.
The system, set up at the beginning to search for cars, can also be used to trace the movement of people and to help in certain cases such as that of the little Anicka Janatkova.
The instrument is currently as big as a box of matches but will soon be the size of a watch.
The case of little Anicka moved a large number of people and they began to look for ways to better protect their children.
Even if the price is to disturb their privacy.
"We are trying to tell everyone that this is not an espionage but only another way to reduce the likelihood of another tragedy," says Petr Pilin of the company Macro Weil, which is one of the suppliers of tracking devices in the Czech market.
"I admit that there may be cases of misuse of such devices, such as putting it in the bag of a person who is not aware, but I have not yet encountered such cases."
"The majority of people are customers who actually buy the product for security reasons," says Pilin.
According to him, children should always know what the "box" is for and how to use it in an emergency.
The child psychologist, Dana Bockova, draws attention that if the child does not want to carry something like this on him, he will get rid of it.
'And even the smaller ones can show great creativity when it comes to getting rid of something on purpose when they don't want to be under control. '
"Mobile phones, which can be cut like these tracking devices, have already brought parents to long expectations," says Bockova.
In her view, the fact that this type of device can help in the event of an attack is highly questionable.
"If it is a prepared abduction, the author will do everything possible to ensure that the child does not have an electronic device to locate it."
"Right now, it's the phone."
"As soon as the tracking devices develop, they (the criminals) will also be looking for them because the sale will be supported by an advertising campaign."
"In such cases criminals will always be ahead of the police," says the psychologist.
She admits, however, that such devices can help in an assault not prepared by a paedophile.
According to Robert Cech of RC Monitoring, which offers tracking services for both cars and people, it is said that having this type of device can help, even if it is destroyed in the case of an assault.
"The device may be configured in such a way that it is in regular emission after a specified period of time."
"If the device is destroyed, it remains the last position of the person concerned."
"The more expensive devices also have an inclinometer that immediately signals the position of the person who slipped and finds himself in the elongated position without moving," says Cech.
According to him, so-called smart mobile phones that are equipped with a navigation system, can offer a comparable service after having formatted it with a special prosoftware.
The problem with current tracking systems is that it is either a device similar to those worn in pendants the size of a match box or to the smallest telephone devices.
We can always lose them.
According to Pilina of Macro Weil, this is why tests are currently being conducted to make devices that look like common digital watches.
"This will have the advantage that the possible attacker will not be able to recognize the tracking device."
"Or after some time, he will find out, which will have given the police a little more time," he adds.
Whether the tracking device is developed in the form of a bracelet or pendant, it will always use the same technology as to track cars.
This is a combination of GPS position acquisition systems (commonly used in self-rescue) and a mobile phone function that alerts the current position of a vehicle.
